    },
    "google_scholar": {
      "label": "Google Scholar",
      "url": "https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=fQtgwlgAAAAJ&hl=zh-CN&oi=ao"
    },
    "about": "I am a researcher at Shanghai AI Laboratory, focusing on agentic and reasoning models, self-evolving agentic systems, frontier benchmarks, and AI for scientific discovery. I received my Ph.D. in Computer and Information Engineering from [**The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Shenzhen**](https://cuhk.edu.cn/en) (CUHKSZ), and received my Bachelor's degree in Physics from the [**University of Chinese Academy of Sciences**](https://english.ucas.ac.cn/) (UCAS).\n\nRecently, I have contributed to open-source models including [**Agents-A1**](https://internscience.github.io/Agents-A1/) (a 35B long-horizon agentic model), [**P1-VL**](https://prime-rl.github.io/P1-VL/) (multimodal physics reasoning models), and [**P1**](https://prime-rl.github.io/P1/) (text-only physics reasoning models). I also lead [**PhysicsMinions**](https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.24855), the first open-model agentic system to reach IPhO-2025 gold-medal level, and [**HiPhO**](https://phyarena.github.io/), the first physics Olympiad benchmark covering 13 recent physics Olympiads from 2024-2025 and used in the Seed 2.0 evaluation leaderboard.\n\nI am actively looking for research collaborators, whether early-career or experienced, especially those from scientific domains. Feel free to reach out."
  },
